THIS IS A STORY ABOUT THE CLARK FAMILY.
THE VIDEO STARTS OUT SAYING HOW IN THE 1940'S NEW YORK PUBLIC LIBRARY CUSTODIANS USUALLY LIVED IN THE BUILDINGS THEY CLEANED.
RAYMOND CLARK WAS ONE SUCH CUSTODIAN.
THE STORY IS TOLD BY RONALD CLARK TO HIS DAUGHTER JAMILAH
HE STARTS OFF TALKING ABOUT BEING AT THE DINNER TABLE WITH HIS PARENTS AND EXCLAIMING HE IS GLAD THEY ARE RICH.
HIS DAD CORRECTS HIM AND SAYS THEY ARE NOT RICH, BUT ARE ACTUALLY POOR.
HIS DAD THEN GETS A JOB AT THE LIBRARY, AND THEY ACTUALLY LIVE THERE.
HE GOES ON TO TALK ABOUT HOW OTHER LIBRARIES YOU WOULD SEE TRASH AND GUM WRAPPERS AND SUCH ON THE FLOOR.
BUT NOT AT HIS DADS LIBRARY, HE TOOK PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND POLISHED EVERY THING TO A SHINE, EVEN THE TOPS OF THE BOOK CASES.
GOES ON TO TALK ABOUT BEING EMBARRASSED ABOUT LIVING IN A LIBRARY AND NEVER BRINGING HIS FRIENDS OVER.
BUT ALSO ENJOYS THAT AT NIGHT AND THE LIBRARY IS EMPTY, HE HAS FREE RUN OF IT.
HE CAN GET UP LATE AND NIGHT AND READ ANYTHING HE WANTS.
GOES ON TO COLLEGE, AND AFTER BECOMES A PROFESSOR AT A COLLEGE.
HE BRINGS HIS DAD IN TO SEE HIS CLASS ROOM, AND SAYS HIS DAD DOESNT SAY MUCH.
BUT HE SEES THIS LOOK ONE HIS DADS FACE OF PURE PROUDNESS.
SO GLAD HIS SON OVER CAME BEING POOR, AND TOOK IT UPON HIM SELF TO DO SOMETHING GOOD WITH HIS LIFE.
HE ACCREDITS IT ALL TO LIVING IN A LIBRARY AND TAKING THE INITIATIVE TO READ AND LEARN FROM THE BOOKS HE HAD ACCESS TO.
VIDEO TALKS ABOUT HOW IN THE 1940S, CUSTODIANS WHO WORK IN THE NEW YORK PUBLIC LIBRARIES OFTEN TIMES LIVED IN THE BUILDING.
TALKS ABOUT THE CLARK FAMILY WHO WAS ONE SUCH FAMILY.
THEY FATHER OF THE FAMILY TOOK GREAT PRIDE IN HIS WORK AND MADE SURE EVERYTHING WAS SPOTLESS AND WAXED
THE SON OF THE FAMILY WOULD READ ALL THE BOOKS HE COULD LATE INTO THE NIGHT.
HE WENT ON TO GRADUATE COLLEGE AND BECAME A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
HIS FATHER WAS VERY PROUD OF HIM AND WHAT HE WAS ABLE TO ACCOMPLISH
